1️⃣ 1–2 cup deseeded watermelon

Happy 4th of July babes! ❤️Hope you all enjoy this DELICIOUS SMOOTHIE recipe! And for all my pregnant mommy’s out there.. I explain the benefits 📝 of each ingredient and how it can help while creating your little nugget! 👶🏼 I’ve listed the shake below.. THIS IS FOR ALL MY CHOCOLATE LOVERS OUT THERE:

1 large banana frozen 
2 tablespoons of natural peanut butter 
2 dates pited 
1 table unsweetened cocoa powder 
1 cup of almond milk 
1 tablespoon of cacao nibs (for the chocolate effect) 
1 tablespoon hemps seeds 
1 scoop #Livbody chocolate mocha protein

Use code Paige20 for 20% off @livbody 🤤

Yep! You heard it first… “The FITIN5 platform is very realistic and achievable when you are determined!” - Rima Fany

Rima Fany also goes on to say “The @fitin5challenge personally helped me develop a better relationship with food and made me realize that exercise is not a punishment. It actually makes me feel good from the inside out! I loved the challenge also because Paige actually lived and went through similar struggles.. (as we are both moms) So it was assuring and relatable that this program set realistic goals and expectations. Thank you Paige and team!” - @rimafany

Rimy your 5 week transformation speaks VOLUMES! 🔥 Not only have you gained more confidence but you’re also glowing with self satisfaction! Thank you for allowing me and the FITIN5 be apart of your journey!

Next challenge starts August 1st — GROUP 1 is already full and closed. Open spots available in group 2 and 3 only. Use promo code: HAPPYBIRTHDAY for $34 off!

node.text:
It’s Monday and we have 5 days until the new month and 5 months until the new year! 😳

How is your year going? What goals have you set out to achieve for 2021? I dare you to dig deep within yourself and discover what you would still like to have happen in your life this year. What will YOU write for the rest of the chapters…..

Aim higher than you think can be done. Finish this year stronger, braver and even more unstoppable. REALLY TRY… REALLY PUT FORTH THE EFFORT (in ALL that you do, not just somethings) Because as they say “if you want something you’ve never had - you have to do something you’ve never done.” Though no one can go back and make a brand new start.. anyone can start and make a brand new ending! How much meaning does life bring when you’re in love with your comfort zone!? You don’t know how much you’re capable of until you GO and until you DO. You are a powerful force. Let’s finish this year with courage and determination!
— — — — — — — — — —
Outfit from @shefit #shefitpartner 💙🤍❤️
Top: NEW Ultimate Sports Bra in Flame Red
Bottom: Boss Leggings in Sodalite Blue 
- Side note: I am so OBSESSED with #Shefit Zip, Cinch, Lift patented technology and their leggings fit like a glove! What are your FAVORITE COLORS to wear? I love wearing red and blue! What about you….? 😍

node.text:
Let’s do a fun Summer Giveaway!!
I’ve partnered up with my F A V E Tanning company @rossaselftanning to give a couple lucky winners FREE ROSSA products from their site. This giveaway is today and tomorrow only so act fast.💨 It’s easy and super simple:  just follow me, @Rossaselftanning and tag a few friends below. BONUS: Rossa will also be throwing in some of their super duper cute tanks. 😍

Win Rossa’s best selling products. See below to enter.

1. LIKE this post 👍⁠
2. FOLLOW @Rossaselftanning AND @Paigehathaway
3. TAG A FRIEND who would love @rossaselftanning, ⁠the more people you tag the higher your chances of winning!

Contest end on Tuesday 7/19 at 11:59pm PST. Winners will be contacted via private DM and announced on my Instagram only. We would never ask you for your personal banking information. I’ll choose winners Wednesday. Contest is not affiliated with Instagram! Let’s beat skin cancer together and Good luck!✨⁠

node.text: They used to say lifting weights make you look “manly” 🙄 I actually thought that… did you used to think that too?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Paige Hathaway on July 15, 2021 tagging @aflannery26, and @fitin5challenge. May be an image of 2 people, people standing and text.

node.text:
What an incredible achievement by Ashley Flannery who says “After having 2 children and multiple cesarean sections, working out was not the easiest to maintain and achieve. This challenge was able to give me the confidence and my body back the way that I wished for.” - @aflannery26

Ashley… What an inspiration you are to me and so many other woman! I am so happy you trusted in the @Fitin5challenge and myself! I am also glad you trusted in yourself and in the process. You are living proof that hard work, consistency and dedication always wins!!

Next challenge starts August 1st and is already half way full — HURRY, TAP IN BIO AND EMAIL ME TODAY!
